5. Experimental Results

The Random Forest intrusion detection model was trained using the generated IoT network dataset.

The model achieved the following performance metrics:

• Accuracy: 95%
• Precision: 94%
• Recall: 93%

The system successfully detected malicious traffic patterns such as abnormal packet volumes and suspicious connection attempts.

The penetration testing module also successfully identified open network ports, allowing the detection of exposed services.

The SOC dashboard effectively visualized network traffic activity and generated alerts when suspicious behavior was detected.

6. Results and Discussion

The integration of machine learning with real-time monitoring significantly improves the detection of network attacks in IoT environments.

Compared to traditional rule-based systems, machine learning models can detect previously unseen attack patterns by analyzing traffic behavior.

The SOC dashboard provides administrators with a centralized monitoring interface that displays security alerts, device status, and network statistics.

The penetration testing module enhances security by identifying exposed services that could be exploited by attackers.

The confusion matrix shows the classification performance of the Random Forest model. The model correctly classifies both normal and malicious traffic with high accuracy.

7. Conclusion

This research presented a machine learning-driven cybersecurity framework designed for IoT and smart city wireless networks. The system integrates intrusion detection, penetration testing, and visualization into a unified security monitoring platform.

The Random Forest classifier demonstrated high detection accuracy in identifying malicious network activities. The SOC dashboard enables real-time monitoring and rapid response to potential threats.

The proposed framework provides an effective solution for enhancing the security of IoT-based smart city infrastructures.

8. Future Work

Future improvements to the proposed system may include:

• Integration of deep learning models such as LSTM for improved anomaly detection
• Real-time packet analysis for live network monitoring
• Deployment in real smart city IoT environments
• Integration with large-scale cybersecurity threat intelligence systems

